article.headline: Old Dominion 73, Toledo 70
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio (AP) -- Brian Henderson hit two free throws with 10 seconds left to help Old Dominion hold off Toledo 73-70 on Saturday night. Toledo (14-11), which had led by as many as 10 points midway through the second half, had its 15-game home winning streak snapped. Valdas Vasylius scored 22 points and had 10 rebounds for the Monarchs (21-7), with Drew Williamson adding 14 points. Williamson's 3-pointer with just over 7 minutes left put Old Dominion ahead to stay, although the Rockets pulled to within a point three more times -- the last when Justin Ingram hit a 3-pointer with 11 seconds left to cut the lead to 71-70. Henderson was fouled by Jonathan Amos on the inbounds pass, with Henderson hitting both foul shots. Kashif Payne missed a 3-pointer with 2 seconds remaining. Ingram led Toledo with 25 points, with Florentino Valencia adding 10.
